Problem: Remove Element
Topic: Arrays, Two Pointers
Difficulty: Easy

Approach:
Traverse the array and overwrite elements not equal to the given value using a pointer k. Increment k only when a valid element is found, effectively compacting the array in-place.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(1)

Code:
class Solution {
public:
    int removeElement(vector<int>& nums, int val) {
      int k=0;
      for( int i=0;i<nums.size();i++){
      if(nums[i]!=val){
        nums[k]=nums[i];
        k++;
      }
    }
    return k;
    }
};
